<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="344" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1843,2014]" pageId="12" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,560,1915,1941]" pageId="12" pageNumber="344">Habitat (as in Indian records).</emphasis>
Marine, intertidal; fine and medium sands, 
<quantity box="[1049,1117,1915,1942]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="344" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
below surface near mid-water level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="345" pageId="12" pageNumber="344" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1843,2014]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,537]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="345" pageId="12" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1987,2013]" pageId="12" pageNumber="344">Distribution.</emphasis>
Originally described from North Europe, the species was subsequently reported from the Mediterranean Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[318,410,151,177]" name="Somalia" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Somalia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[465,523,151,177]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">India</collectingCountry>
(Bay of Bengal). According to Hummon (2010) the species is also present along the Pacific coast the 
<collectingCountry box="[383,443,187,213]" name="United States of America" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">USA</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="345" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[353,411,223,249]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">India</collectingCountry>
the species has been found at least twice; however, morphometric data were provided only once, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ganapati, P. N. &amp; Rao, G. C." box="[251,515,259,286]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" pagination="214 - 225" refId="ref11834" refString="Ganapati, P. N. &amp; Rao, G. C. (1967) On some marine interstitial gastrotrichs from the beach sands of Waltair coast. Proceeding of Indian Academy of Sciences, 66 B, 214 - 225." type="journal article" year="1967">Ganapati &amp; Rao (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, who state that the Indian specimens conform to the original description. However, by comparing morphometric parameters of the specimens from the Baltic (original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Remane, A." box="[1264,1428,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" pagination="473 - 478" refId="ref13534" refString="Remane, A. (1934) Die Gastrotrichen des Kustengrundwassers von Schilksee. Schriften des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins fur Schleswig Holstein, 20, 473 - 478." type="journal article" year="1934">Remane, 1934</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[201,261,331,357]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">India</collectingCountry>
, the Indian specimens appear slightly larger in body length (160-180 μm vs 130-150 μm), they bear a longer pharynx (50 μm vs 40 μm) and a shorter furca (40 μm vs 47 μm). On the other hand, the Mediterranean specimens are larger for body (180-222 μm) and furca (55-67 μm) length (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruppert, E. E." box="[1050,1209,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref13618" refString="Ruppert, E. E. (1979) Morphology and systematics of the Xenotrichulidae (Gastrotricha, Chaetonotida). Mikrofauna des Meeresbodens, 76, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1979">Ruppert 1979</bibRefCitation>
). In our opinion the highlighted differences among populations suggest another possible case of species lumping, and call for additional analyses to support the current hypothesis that the different populations belong to the same species. In the meantime, the presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Remane" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[328,497,511,537]" family="Xenotrichulidae" genus="Heteroxenotrichula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="13" pageNumber="345" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis box="[328,497,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">H. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[533,591,511,537]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="345">India</collectingCountry>
should be considered only provisional.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
